Internship takes place in one of the selected conflict regions in cooperation with the receiving host institution. During the internship students are informed about the conflict dynamics and settlement perspectives. In-class training lessons include meetings with local experts, politicians and international mediators.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim is to study root causes and conflict dynamics in one of the selected conflict regions. It takes place in the form of study trip.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completing this internship, the students - will gain a comprehensive knowledge about conflict dynamics and settlement perspectives; - will understand the role of international diplomacy in conflict management and know how to use these practical skills in real life.
